    "img": "https://imgix.ranker.com/user_node_img/129/2573587/original/gambit-comic-book-characters-photo-u11?auto=format&q=60&fit=crop&fm=pjpg&dpr=2&crop=faces&h=150&w=150",
    "description": "A gambit (from Italian gambetto, the act of tripping someone with the leg to make them fall) is a chess opening in which a player sacrifices material with the aim of achieving a subsequent positional advantage. The word gambit is also sometimes used to describe similar tactics used by politicians or business people in a struggle with rivals in their respective fields, for example \"The early election was a risky gambit by Theresa May\"."
